title: 9News Sydney | Thursday December 11 | Full Episode
description: Georgie Gardner leads the bulletin with major news as a wild police chase in Sydney's south-west ends in a devastating crash, leaving one young woman fighting for her life. Police have arrested a teenage driver out on bail. Plus, a massive weapons bust across south-west Sydney. Sydney drivers will now have to pay tolls in both directions on the Harbour Bridge and Tunnel, but the $60 weekly toll cap is being made permanent. In court news, former Jetstar pilot Greg Lynn wins a stunning appeal against his murder conviction, and Tom Silvagni, the son of an AFL legend, is found guilty of rape. Internationally, the U.S. is proposing major changes to tourist visa rules requiring social media data, and an escalation of tensions sees a Venezuelan oil tanker forcibly seized by the US. Finally, a spectacular brush with death for a skydiver in Far North Queensland.
